{"id":774666,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Tsirelson","text":"Boris Semyonovich Tsirelson (May 4, 1950\u00A0\u2013 January 21, 2020) (,) was a Russian\u2013Israeli mathematician. He was a Professor of Mathematics at Tel Aviv University in Israel. He was born in Leningrad. He was known for his discoveries: Tsirelson's bound, Tsirelson space, Tsirelson drift and Gaussian isoperimetric inequality.\nTsirelson, who had cancer, was euthanized on January 21, 2020 in Basel, Switzerland at the age of 69.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Russia","surface_form":"Russia","offset":71},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":79},{"uri":"Mathematician","surface_form":"mathematician","offset":87},{"uri":"Tel_Aviv_University","surface_form":"Tel Aviv University","offset":139},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":162},{"uri":"Leningrad","surface_form":"Leningrad","offset":185},{"uri":"Tsirelson%27s_bound","surface_form":"Tsirelson's bound","offset":230},{"uri":"Tsirelson_space","surface_form":"Tsirelson space","offset":249},{"uri":"Tsirelson_drift","surface_form":"Tsirelson drift","offset":266},{"uri":"Gaussian_isoperimetric_inequality","surface_form":"Gaussian isoperimetric inequality","offset":286},{"uri":"Cancer","surface_form":"cancer","offset":340},{"uri":"Euthanized","surface_form":"euthanized","offset":352},{"uri":"Basel","surface_form":"Basel","offset":386},{"uri":"Switzerland","surface_form":"Switzerland","offset":393}]}